
#  The Windows Instance: Microsoft Windows Server 2012 Base - ami-6f2cf804
#  We will use FTP to pull some things from the internet. FTP requires
#  ports. Ports 21, 80, 443, 50000-51000
#
#  Disable firewall
#  go to Administrative Tools on the startup window
#  open “Windows Firewall with Advanced Security”

#  Download chrome rather than using IE
#
#  Use chrome to download Cygwin
#
#  Setup cygwin install and in addition to the base system get these packages:
#      wget, curl, unzip, git
#     

# install java

#  wget http://stevemansour.com/accord/jdk-8u51-windows-x64.exe
#    this can be done, with the "/s" option
#

#  next, update the path so that java can be found:
#  Click Start, then Control Panel, then System and Security, then System.
#
#  Click Advanced system settings, click the Advanced tab, then Environment Variables.
#
#  Add the location of the bin folder of the JDK installation for the PATH variable in System Variables. The following is a typical value for the PATH variable:
#
#  C:\WINDOWS\system32;C:\WINDOWS;C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.7.0\bin
